Parapodia with chaetal lobes slightly as long as wide, truncate (
Fig. 7C
); dorsal cirri with cirrophores smooth, about twice as long as wide; cirrostyles basally cylindrical, annulated throughout their length. Ventral cirri regularly corrugated, surpassing chaetal lobe.

